<inglise> (11) Whereas paragraph 17 of the conclusions of the Luxembourg European Council of 12 and 13 December 1997 provides that financial support to the countries involved in the enlargement process will be based, in the allocation of aid, on the principle of equal treatment, independently of time of accession, with particular attention being paid to countries with the greatest need; </inglise>
<eesti> 11) Euroopa &Uuml;lemkogu 12. ja 13. detsembri 1997. aasta Luxembourgi istungj&auml;rgu otsuste l&otilde;ikega 17 n&auml;hakse ette, et laienemisprotsessi kaasatud riikidele antav rahaline toetus rajaneb toetuse jagamisel v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;ttel, s&otilde;ltumata &uuml;hinemise ajast, p&ouml;&ouml;rates erilist t&auml;helepanu enim tuge vajavatele riikidele; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) Whereas the rates of assistance provided from the Community under ISPA should be set in order to strengthen the leverage effect of resources, promote co-financing and the use of private sources of finance and to take account of the capacity of measures to generate substantial net revenue; </inglise>
<eesti> 12) tuleks kinnitada ISPA kaudu antava &uuml;henduse abi m&auml;&auml;rad, et t&otilde;hustada ressursside kasutamisest saadavat m&otilde;ju, soodustada kaasfinantseerimist ja erasektori rahastamisallikate kasutamist ning v&otilde;tta arvesse meetmetest saadavat v&otilde;imalikku puhastulu; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) Whereas, as regards Community assistance, maximum transparency must be ensured in the implementation of financial assistance, and stringent controls must be applied to the use of appropriations; </inglise>
<eesti> 13) &uuml;henduse abi puhul tuleb tagada &uuml;henduse finantsabi rakendamise selgus ja arusaadavus ning kontrollida rangelt assigneeringute kasutamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (14) Whereas, in the interest of the proper management of Community assistance granted under ISPA, provision should be made for effective methods of appraising, monitoring, evaluating and controlling operations, specifying the principle governing the evaluation, defining the nature of and the rules governing the monitoring, and laying down the action to be taken in response to irregularities or failures to comply with one of the conditions laid down when assistance under ISPA was granted; </inglise>
<eesti> 14) ISPA kaudu antava &uuml;henduse abi n&otilde;uetekohaseks juhtimiseks tuleks ette n&auml;ha meetmete eelhindamise, j&auml;relevalve, j&auml;relhindamise ja kontrollimise meetodid, esitades j&auml;relhindamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted ning m&auml;&auml;ratledes j&auml;relevalve olemuse ja eeskirjad, ning n&auml;ha ette meetmed juhuks, kui eiratakse eeskirju v&otilde;i ei t&auml;ideta m&otilde;nda ISPA kaudu abi andmise tingimustest; </eesti>
<inglise> (15) Whereas, during the transitional period from 1 January 1999 until 31 December 2001, each reference made to the euro should as a general rule also be read as a reference to the euro as a monetary unit as in Article 2, second sentence, of Council Regulation (EC) No 974/98 of 3 May 1998 on the introduction of the euro(10); </inglise>
<eesti> 15) &uuml;leminekuperioodil 1. jaanuarist 1999 kuni 31. detsembrini 2001 tuleks k&otilde;iki viiteid eurole &uuml;ldjuhul k&auml;sitada viitena eurole kui raha&uuml;hikule vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 3. mai 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 974/98 (euro kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta) artikli 2 teisele lausele; </eesti>
